steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"9hean","text":"Standard Operating Procedure to outline the process for obtaining, processing, and storing peripheral lymphatic vessel samples collected for the HuBMAP Lymphatic TMC.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b3hgg","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"au98g","text":"The vessels are collected through a permanent removal of right axillary lymphatic vessel during lymphedema surgery from patients with malignant neoplasm of right female breast.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b66tq","text":"Patients with age \u003e18 years from any race (White, Black, Hispanic, and Asian) are included. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"koiq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5852n","text":"Patients are excluded if they have one of the following characteristic:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"61v4u","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ec014","text":"Have a known underlying lymphatic disease.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5vato","text":"Suffer from a chronic inflammatory condition (e.g. RA).","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ftnfo","text":"Have ahistory of filarial infection.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"efe2a","text":"Have a history of allergy to lymphazurin blue.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2r51d","text":"Are actively breastfeeding.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"tuia","text":"Have a history of sensitivity to triphenylmethane.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"80m5u","text":"Have a history of systemic therapeutic treatment (e.g. chemotherapy).","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cp9el","text":"Have a history of pathology at anticipated site of lymphatic vessel harvest.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1np8s","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5mfqs","text":"Following confirmation of the above inclusion and exclusion criteria by a study coordinator, the patient is informed about the study and provides informed consent according to the BIDMC IRB criteria.Â ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8nfgt","text":"\nDonors accepting to participate into the study are assigned an ascending 3-digit number (beginning with 001)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7o19b","text":"The following information is recorded per study participant: Age, Sex, BMI, Hospitalization Time, Comorbidities, and Clinical history from the OMR.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e5mvq","text":"During the planned radial forearm free flap, 3 injections of 0.1cc of ICGare injected into the fascia 2cm apart proximal to the radial styloid.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e1k2m","text":"Identified lymphatic vessels are harvested (2x5mm, or longer) with microsurgical scissors and microclips applied to free lymphatic ends.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ee14u","text":"A 9-0 suture (peri-adventitial) is placed at the 12 oâclock position (i.e. the side of the vessel facing the axillary vein) â on the side farthest from the heart, to mark orientation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fldpj","text":"The distance from thevessel to the edge of the axillary vein is recorded.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4diqj","text":"The peri-lymphatic adipose tissue of the lymphatic vessel is removed as closely to the vessel as possible.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"38ula","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1shc6","text":"    ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":2,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"995ns","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"35B64D30860D11EDB1F30FA01FC9F47D","height":484.37272727272716,"id":326594,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":148,"offset":0,"style":"bold"}],"key":"984q3","text":"Fig 1a: Marking of lymphatic vessel with the use of a 9-0 suture (peri-adventitial) at the 12 oâclock position, on the side furthest from the heart.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/png","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"Fig1Left.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j88ebybv7.jpg","shadow":true,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j88cbybv7.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j88dbybv7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j88bbybv7.webp","width":319.0479041916167}},"1":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"9CA577A0860D11EDB1F30FA01FC9F47D","height":444,"id":326598,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":70,"offset":0,"style":"bold"}],"key":"5tsaf","text":"Fig 1b: Marking the distance below the axillary vein for orientation. ","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/png","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"fig1right2.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j88ibybv7.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j88gbybv7.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j88hbybv7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j88fbybv7.webp","width":550}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7ejni","text":"In a petri dish, carefully coat fresh tissue sample with room temperature OCT. Using a spatula, place the OCT-coated tissue into an appropriately sized cryomold.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8k5tb","text":"Cover the tissue completely with OCT. Label the cryomold to mark the orientation of the tissue.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cuekq","text":"Using forceps, lower the embedded tissue into the isopentane without fully submerging.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1tffe","text":"Keep cryomold in contact with isopentane until the OCT has solidified and turned white. Once frozen, place the cryomold on powdered dry ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1mlq8","text":"Store frozen embedded tissue in a sealed container at -80C or liquid nitrogen for long-term storage.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
